        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>CHARLES HOFFMAN&#44;<lb/>
                ATTORNEY AT LAW&#44;				SUBJECT&#44; Jewish Theolog. Seminary<lb/>
                S. E. COR. FIFTH &#38; CHESTNUT STS.<lb/>
                &#40;DREXEL BUILDING.&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>PHILADELPHIA&#44; March 28th 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais.<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#58;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>In taking my notes of meeting of the<lb/> convention&#44; I used a blank book at the suggestion of some of<lb/> the students&#44; which after inquiry of Dr Drachman&#44; I find is<lb/> of use as a roll book at the seminary.  I would like to send this<lb/> back&#44; and thought if you contemplated visiting the institution shortly&#44;<lb/> you might not be unwilling to take the book with you&#44; or if any other of<lb/> the Philadelphia Trustees were going to New York&#44; the same might be done by them.<lb/>  Will you kindly advise me if this is the case&#44; and if it would be convenient for you<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to take it.  Otherwise I can express it&#44; or take such other action<lb/> as you may see fit to suggest.<lb/></p>
            <p>Very Respectfully Yours<lb/>
                Charles Hoffman<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
